“Code as Constitution” trend: Smart contracts embed the full rule set so execution is automatic and tamper-proof (AI auditors often verify proof-of-work before payouts).

Strengths: Prevents whale capture, reduces low-participation chaos, and scales self-governance.
Risks: Overly rigid constitutions can stifle adaptation; initial ratification must be legitimate.
